    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.8.0-dev-872-gbccb5de89\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nALL\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 36 Linux\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n1. Call `vim.lsp.buf_detach_client({bufnr}, {client_id})` programmatically.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nLSP client should detach from buffer silently. No alerts or notifications should be displayed to the user.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nA notification pops up every time an LSP client is programmatically detached from the buffer. \r\n\r\nThis is distracting for users who deliberately detach the LSP client in `InsertMode` or `Zen Mode`.\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
